{
  "text": "The use of information and communication technology (ICT) is becoming progressively more widespread throughout various sectors including education, business as well as agriculture [CITATION_1] . ICT as an extension tool could enhance the flow of information in the application of agricultural extension services. Communication exposure of SAAOs towards e-agriculture scores ranged from 3 to 17 against the possible range of 0 to 36. Based on observed maximum and minimum communication exposure score and number of categories, the following categories were formulated in the Table 3 .",
